Finally tracked down the cause.  We have a custom authentication/login module that was using it&#39;s own copy of the Jackson libraries (jackson-core-2.13.4.jar, jackson-databind-2.13.4.2.jar, jackson-annotations-2.13.4.jar).  I removed them from **module.xml** and instead added the following to the dependencies in module.xml:
```
&lt;module name=&quot;org.jboss.resteasy.resteasy-jaxrs&quot;/&gt;
&lt;module name=&quot;org.jboss.resteasy.resteasy-jackson2-provider&quot;/&gt;
```
After restarting Wildfly, the payloads were returned as expected.  I did use the `-D&quot;resteasy.preferJacksonOverJsonB&quot;=&quot;true&quot;` setting as suggested by James (thank you!).

